      "content": "Yes, I am agreeing that the current flagging mechanism is problematic because it has demonstrated disproportionate bias against specific student groups. Moving toward a community-based approach acknowledges that purely technological surveillance can perpetuate systemic unfairness. Therefore, ending the surveillance is a necessary step toward building a more equitable safety culture. The focus should shift from monitoring individuals to fostering a safer community environment.",
